                <div class="col-sm-9 text-justify">
                    <h3>SUSAN ERNER, RMT</h3>
                    <p>Susan is a graduate of the 2200hr program at the Professional Institute of Massage Therapy in Calgary, and the Freiburg Teaching Institute of Physical Therapy in Germany.</p>
                    <p>She has been a Massage Therapist since 2007 and absolutely loves sharing the healing power of Massage Therapy with her clients. She believes that Massage Therapy plays a key role in dealing with many of life’s stressors and that it is essential for long-term health and well-being. Through education, knowledge, and experience, Susan empowers her clients to achieve optimal health and overall wellness.</p>
                    <p>Susan spends her free time exploring the Canadian outdoors with her dog, reading, cuddling with her cats, knitting and learning new massage modalities.</p>
                </div>
                <div class="col-sm-3 text-center pad_top1 hidden-xs">
