                    <h3>CLARISSA MCANDREWS, LEAD RMT</h3>
                    <p>Clarissa graduated from Mount Royal University’s 2200 hour program and worked as a full time massage therapist since. She has taken on a role as a Teaching Assistant in Mount Royal Universities Massage Therapy program. She has an ever growing passion for advancing her knowledge in the massage research community, is a strong supporter of a healthy lifestyle, the use of natural alternatives to healing ones ailments and the prevention of injury through massage. When working with clients, she believes that treatment continues at home, through the use of home care programs specifically designed for each individual.</p>
                    <p>Clarissa specializes in deep tissue work, sports, therapeutic, pre and postnatal treatments and relaxation massage. On a more personal level, Clarissa loves to be outdoors in her spare time, from cross country or downhill mountain biking in the summer to snowboarding in the winter.</p>
